WEBVTT

00:03.558 --> 00:05.159
Oh, what do you mean
he ghosted you?

00:05.161 --> 00:08.762
We went on a couple of dates
and had fun and then nothing.

00:08.764 --> 00:10.097
Nothing?

00:10.099 --> 00:12.666
He didn't respond to any of
my texts or my phone calls.

00:12.668 --> 00:14.235
He's not interested.

00:14.237 --> 00:15.202
Why?

00:15.204 --> 00:16.537
You tell me.

00:16.539 --> 00:17.571
I have no idea.

00:17.573 --> 00:20.741
Well, maybe you
did that thing.

00:20.743 --> 00:21.742
What thing?

00:21.744 --> 00:23.210
The thing where you
chew really loud.

00:23.212 --> 00:24.845
I don't chew really loud!

00:24.847 --> 00:27.147
You are the only person that
has a hang-up about that.

00:27.149 --> 00:28.682
If you say so.

00:28.684 --> 00:31.685
DISPATCHER: 12-David, we have
a 10-30, robbery in progress

00:31.687 --> 00:32.820
at Exceptional Deli,

00:32.822 --> 00:35.389
174 West 74th Street.
Oh, come on.

00:35.391 --> 00:36.790
(siren wailing)

00:43.131 --> 00:45.132
You're under arrest.
- Move it.

00:45.134 --> 00:46.834
Anything you say or do
will be used against you

00:46.836 --> 00:48.602
in a court of law.

00:48.604 --> 00:49.904
Thank God you're here.

00:49.906 --> 00:51.305
Follow me.
MAN: If you need an attorney,

00:51.307 --> 00:54.174
one will be provided for you.
This kid tried to rob me.

00:54.176 --> 00:55.142
- Get him off of me!
- You have the right to remain silent.

00:55.144 --> 00:56.810
Billy, what's going on?

00:56.812 --> 00:58.712
Whoa, come over here.
Calm down, calm down.

00:58.714 --> 01:02.182
This man is under arrest
for-for petty larceny, Jamie.

01:02.184 --> 01:04.952
For-for-for stealing
and disobeying an order

01:04.953 --> 01:07.054
and for being a really bad guy.
- Okay.

01:07.056 --> 01:08.622
Okay, Billy. How about this?
Okay, Billy. Calm down.

01:08.624 --> 01:10.224
How about this?
We go outside

01:10.226 --> 01:11.926
and we'll take care
of this, okay?

01:11.928 --> 01:14.261
Uh... stealer!

01:14.263 --> 01:15.496
All right. All right, Billy.
Okay.

01:15.498 --> 01:16.864
All right.

01:16.866 --> 01:19.700
He stole those cigarettes
and-and-and he stole candy.

01:19.702 --> 01:20.868
I don't steal candy.
- Right.

01:20.870 --> 01:23.037
We-we know, we know, Bill,
we know you don't.

01:23.039 --> 01:25.940
But, hey. Hey, Bill.
Bill, hey.

01:25.942 --> 01:28.008
When-when something
like this happens,

01:28.010 --> 01:30.077
what are you supposed to do?

01:30.079 --> 01:31.045
Call...

01:31.047 --> 01:34.415
9-1-1.

01:34.417 --> 01:37.584
Call 911. But-but-but he-he was
going to flee the scene.

01:37.586 --> 01:38.852
He was breaking
the law, Bill,

01:38.854 --> 01:40.614
and you're a good citizen
for trying to help.

01:40.722 --> 01:43.223
Next time, don't put
yourself in harm's way.

01:43.225 --> 01:44.658
Otherwise, you'd be
putting us out of a job.

01:44.660 --> 01:46.459
I don't want to do that.

01:46.461 --> 01:48.061
- You call 911.
- Mm-hmm.

01:48.063 --> 01:50.363
And if they run,
we'll chase 'em, okay?

01:50.365 --> 01:52.198
Are you going to arrest him?

01:52.200 --> 01:53.700
Yeah, he's getting
a desk appearance ticket

01:53.702 --> 01:55.605
and he's gonna have to
explain himself to a judge.

01:55.606 --> 01:57.204
Oh, ho, ho.
Good!

01:57.205 --> 01:58.805
All because
of you, Billy.

01:58.807 --> 02:00.640
But, hey, listen, next time...

02:00.642 --> 02:04.311
Call 911. Call 911
and, uh, don't hold him.

02:04.313 --> 02:05.378
Right.

02:05.380 --> 02:07.614
You be careful out there.
You, too, Billy.

02:10.283 --> 02:11.818
Yeah, you be careful, Bill.

02:14.822 --> 02:17.057
And one more bonus of the job,

02:17.059 --> 02:19.426
you can sit down with
a president, a rock star,

02:19.428 --> 02:21.194
famous athlete,
and a cop.

02:21.196 --> 02:24.364
Whose stories does
everyone want to hear?

02:24.366 --> 02:26.466
The cop's.

02:26.468 --> 02:28.068
Believe it or not, yes.

02:28.070 --> 02:31.204
I've seen it many times,
and I'll tell you why.

02:32.306 --> 02:36.409
Some have happy endings,
some have heartbreaking ones.

02:36.411 --> 02:39.646
But the best ones reveal
the unvarnished truth

02:39.648 --> 02:43.583
of who we really are.

02:43.585 --> 02:46.086
Sounds like you really
miss being a cop.

02:48.889 --> 02:52.959
I miss the job every single day.

02:52.961 --> 02:56.262
But I really, really
miss the bad guys.

02:56.264 --> 02:57.731
(laughing)

02:57.733 --> 03:01.768
Well, by that, I mean, there is
no better feeling for a cop

03:01.770 --> 03:04.571
than slapping the cuffs
on a bad guy

03:04.573 --> 03:06.906
and getting him off the street.

03:06.908 --> 03:08.074
All right, well,
we've taken enough

03:08.076 --> 03:09.242
of the police
commissioner's time,

03:09.244 --> 03:12.545
unless anybody has any last,
final question?

03:12.547 --> 03:15.815
Well, I have a question
for all of you.

03:15.817 --> 03:17.751
How many of you want to be cops?

03:21.689 --> 03:23.823
Anyone?

03:26.594 --> 03:28.728
Yeah.

03:28.730 --> 03:32.265
I want to be the first black
female police commissioner.

03:32.267 --> 03:35.602
(chuckles)
Good for you.

03:35.604 --> 03:38.371
But not 'cause I like cops
or anything like that.

03:40.808 --> 03:42.575
'Cause I want to
change the system.

03:42.577 --> 03:44.978
I want to change
everything about it.

03:44.980 --> 03:47.814
GORMLEY:
Okay, uh, listen up.

03:47.816 --> 03:49.249
We're gonna
exit out this way.

03:49.251 --> 03:51.618
Officer Dubrowski is gonna
take you back downstairs.

03:51.620 --> 03:52.585
Follow him.

03:52.587 --> 03:54.087
Thank you.

03:54.089 --> 03:55.155
Uh, excuse me.

03:55.157 --> 03:57.223
Um, sorry.

03:57.225 --> 03:58.725
Um, what's your name?
- Sophia.

03:58.727 --> 04:01.494
Um, can I give you this?

04:01.496 --> 04:02.996
I'd love it if
you called me.

04:02.998 --> 04:05.198
I'd like to talk to you
some more about this.

04:05.200 --> 04:06.900
Sure. Okay.

04:06.902 --> 04:07.834
Okay.

04:07.836 --> 04:10.069
Thank you.
Oh, thank you.

04:10.071 --> 04:11.538
Thank you.
Good luck, Sophia.

04:11.540 --> 04:12.739
Thanks.

04:17.478 --> 04:19.245
Hey!
- Hi.

04:19.247 --> 04:20.245
You got here early.

04:20.248 --> 04:22.115
Hi, Lieutenant.

04:22.117 --> 04:23.049
Ms. Reagan.

04:23.051 --> 04:24.517
I'm glad I got
to hear that.

04:24.519 --> 04:27.120
I didn't even know
you missed the job.

04:27.122 --> 04:31.658
Well... I do miss
living those stories.

04:31.660 --> 04:34.360
Well, as you can see, nobody
wants to be a cop anymore.

04:34.362 --> 04:36.729
I do.

04:36.731 --> 04:42.168
You do?

04:42.170 --> 04:44.771
What do you know.

04:44.773 --> 04:47.807
I signed up to take
the exam on Monday.

04:47.809 --> 04:49.943
Well... (chuckles)
I'll leave you two.

04:49.945 --> 04:51.044
I'll catch you later, boss.

04:51.046 --> 04:53.112
Yeah.

04:53.114 --> 04:55.248
But I didn't tell Mom yet.

04:55.250 --> 04:56.516
Well, you want it
to be a surprise.

04:56.518 --> 04:59.886
Why don't I think
she'll be happy about it?

04:59.888 --> 05:01.788
Why wouldn't she be
happy about it?

05:01.790 --> 05:04.090
It's the family business.

05:04.092 --> 05:07.494
Because it's the
family business.

05:10.397 --> 05:11.831
Let's talk.

05:11.833 --> 05:15.168
All I'm asking is that you
request that he be remanded.

05:15.170 --> 05:16.135
It's not my case.

05:16.137 --> 05:17.270
What do you mean
it's not your case?

05:17.272 --> 05:19.305
You're the
supervising ADA.

05:19.307 --> 05:21.407
Last time I checked, supervising
means you're the boss.

05:21.409 --> 05:22.909
Good morning, Anthony.

05:22.911 --> 05:24.544
Used to be.
- (sighs) Yeah.

05:24.546 --> 05:26.179
Nice to see you, too.

05:26.181 --> 05:28.314
We need to speak to the witness
in the Sanchez murder case.

05:28.316 --> 05:29.516
Uh, the vic's grandmother.
(phone rings)

05:29.518 --> 05:31.584
Yeah, Rosalie Morales.
I remember her.

05:31.586 --> 05:34.454
Yeah, and I want to make sure
that she's prepped for court.

05:34.456 --> 05:36.289
Erin Reagan.

05:38.025 --> 05:39.659
Ah, right.

05:39.661 --> 05:41.027
I'll be right over.

05:41.029 --> 05:42.862
Can you speak to
the witness on your own?

05:42.864 --> 05:44.063
DANNY: Think you
can handle that

05:44.065 --> 05:45.398
all by yourself, tough guy?

05:45.400 --> 05:46.699
Yeah, well, at least I don't
have to come up here

05:46.701 --> 05:48.034
begging my sister
for favors.

05:48.036 --> 05:50.036
You know, I remember when you
used to knock down doors.

05:50.038 --> 05:51.070
Now you just open doors.

05:51.072 --> 05:52.305
ERIN:
Guys, guys.

05:52.307 --> 05:53.706
You know how juvenile you sound?

05:56.210 --> 05:57.210
Thank you, Anthony.

05:57.212 --> 05:58.878
Let me know how it goes.

06:00.648 --> 06:03.550
Don't forget the door
on the way out.

06:07.922 --> 06:09.455
(intercom buzzes)

06:16.830 --> 06:18.398
Excuse me.

06:18.400 --> 06:21.267
Have you seen this woman around?
Ms. Morales?

06:21.269 --> 06:25.405
The massage parlor, upstairs.

06:25.407 --> 06:27.874
Thank you.

06:32.079 --> 06:33.546
Hello?

06:33.548 --> 06:35.982
(arguing in Spanish)

06:37.000 --> 06:43.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

06:45.426 --> 06:47.393
(yelling in Spanish)

06:52.132 --> 06:53.266
(yelling in Spanish)

06:56.870 --> 06:59.305
(both yell)

07:02.009 --> 07:03.943
(groans)

